The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Not just commercial art

 Advertising as a medium of creative communication has had a tremendous impact on our lives in recent times. Translating a marketing or selling concept into a tangible form, designers graphically depict a message that ultimately has the power to influence our buying decisions. Masterstrokes, the ongoing exhibition of original artworks of key advertising campaigns, is an effort to bring to the forefront the talents of professionals who create powerful, enduring advertising messages. Bringing together and showcasing designs developed by artists and art directors of leading advertising agencies, the show features artworks and design layouts of advertisements mainly created for traditional print media, as also for leaflets, posters and outdoor campaigns. Participating artists: Ardhendu Dutta, Aloke Chatterjee, Mrityunjoy Chatterjee, Subrato Bhowmik, Biman Nandy, Arindam Nandy, Arthur Cardozo, Lalit Maiti, Dipankar Sarkar and Nitai Das.

 Event: An exhibition of original advertising artworks

 When: Till April 30, 11am - 8 pm

 Where: Gallery Kanishka?s, 2/1 Hindustan Road




